-GOOD MORNING.

05:23.497 --> 05:24.454
-HEY.

05:24.585 --> 05:25.934
-I GOT A MESSAGE YOU CALLED.

05:26.064 --> 05:28.328
HOPEFULLY YOU'VE HAD
A CHANGE OF MIND.

05:30.808 --> 05:32.506
-CHIEF, I WANT YOU
TO SEE SOMETHING.

05:34.899 --> 05:36.814
-WHAT'S THIS?

05:36.945 --> 05:38.120
-THE EMPLOYMENT REQUIREMENTS
FOR THE POLICE DEPARTMENT,

05:38.250 --> 05:39.687
THE FIRE DEPARTMENT, AND
THE STATE LIFEGUARDS.

05:39.817 --> 05:41.558
I HAVE HIGHLIGHTED THE
VISION REQUIREMENTS

05:41.689 --> 05:42.516
FOR EACH DEPARTMENT.

05:43.255 --> 05:46.998
-20/40, 20/40, 20/40.

05:47.129 --> 05:49.174
-WE'RE ONE OF THE FEW
DEPARTMENTS THAT STILL REQUIRE

05:49.305 --> 05:51.394
20/30 VISION FOR
INCOMING PERSONNEL.

05:52.134 --> 05:53.309
AND DO YOU KNOW
WHEN THE LAST TIME

05:53.440 --> 05:55.050
OUR STANDARDS WERE REVISED?

05:55.703 --> 05:58.183
-WELL I'M GOING TO SAY
LATE 70'S, EARLY 80'S.

05:58.314 --> 06:02.231
-1978, A LIFETIME
AGO WHEN YOU CONSIDER

06:02.362 --> 06:04.625
THE ADVANCES MADE
IN CONTACT LENSES.

06:04.755 --> 06:07.279
AS A RESULT WE ARE
LOSING AN UNTOLD NUMBER

06:07.410 --> 06:12.241
OF HIGHLY QUALIFIED INDIVIDUALS,
LIKE MANNY GUTIERREZ.

06:12.372 --> 06:15.244
OH, BY THE WAY HIS
FILE'S IN THERE AS WELL.

06:15.375 --> 06:16.898
-YOU KNOW THIS
IS HIGHLY UNUSUAL.

06:17.028 --> 06:18.290
-BUT WITHIN YOUR
AUTHORITY IF DONE

06:18.421 --> 06:20.031
FOR THE GOOD
OF THE DEPARTMENT.

06:20.162 --> 06:22.033
-OH I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
WAIVING THE REQUIREMENT.

06:22.164 --> 06:24.296
I'M TALKING ABOUT
A 25 YEAR VETERAN

06:24.427 --> 06:26.995
GOING TO BAT FOR
A ROOKIE WASHOUT.

06:27.125 --> 06:29.476
NOW THIS IS SOMETHING THAT
YOU EXPECT FROM A CAPTAIN,

06:29.606 --> 06:32.043
NOT FROM A NORMAL,
EVERYDAY LIFEGUARD.

06:32.174 --> 06:35.177
-THIS IS NOT ABOUT
ME, IT'S ABOUT MANNY.

06:35.307 --> 06:37.527
-YES, AND WHERE WOULD MANNY
BE IF YOU WERE STILL SITTING

06:37.658 --> 06:41.313
IN YOUR TOWER WATCHING THE
WATER, RECAPTURING YOUR YOUTH?

06:42.271 --> 06:44.795
THESE KIDS NEED MORE THAN
TANNING TIPS OR A FEW PEARLS

06:44.926 --> 06:48.320
OF YOUR WISDOM, MITCH,
THEY NEED YOUR LEADERSHIP.

06:51.280 --> 06:56.328
-[MUMBLING]

07:01.029 --> 07:02.247
-ANYONE WANT TO GO
OVER THIS MANUAL?

07:02.378 --> 07:03.553
I NEVER REALIZED
YOU HAD TO KNOW

07:03.684 --> 07:05.599
THIS MUCH STUFF
TO BE A LIFEGUARD.

07:05.729 --> 07:06.861
-TELL ME ABOUT IT.

07:06.991 --> 07:09.516
-WE CAN STUDY TONIGHT,
I'M GOING IN THE WATER.

07:10.430 --> 07:13.258
-ME TOO, NEWMIE SAYS I GOTTA
WORK ON MY INS AND OUTS.

07:13.389 --> 07:14.434
-YOUR WHAT?

07:14.564 --> 07:15.739
-COME ON, LET'S GO.

07:16.436 --> 07:18.786
-UH, IF YOU'RE GOING FOR A
SWIM, TAKE A RESCUE CAN WITH YOU

07:18.916 --> 07:20.701
SO YOU CAN GET THE FEEL OF
WHAT IT'S LIKE IN THE WATER.

07:20.831 --> 07:21.876
-OKAY.

07:30.624 --> 07:32.626
-HEY WAIT, I CAN'T
FIGURE THIS OUT.

07:32.756 --> 07:34.628
-WELL WHICH SIDE DO YOU
BREATHE ON WHEN YOU SWIM?

07:35.193 --> 07:36.891
-THE LEFT.

07:37.021 --> 07:38.196
-OKAY, THEN YOU WANNA PUT
IT OVER YOUR RIGHT SHOULDER.

07:38.849 --> 07:39.676
LIKE THAT.

07:39.807 --> 07:40.677
-GREAT.

07:41.461 --> 07:43.114
SO, WHAT DO YOU
GUYS THINK OF HOBIE?

07:43.245 --> 07:44.376
-HOBIE BUCHANNON?

07:44.507 --> 07:45.465
-MITCH'S SON?

07:45.595 --> 07:46.944
-HE'S STILL IN HIGH SCHOOL.

07:47.075 --> 07:48.772
-BUT HE'S
GRADUATING THIS YEAR.

07:48.903 --> 07:51.514
HE OFFERED TO BE MY PERSONAL
TUTOR FOR ROOKIE SCHOOL.

07:51.645 --> 07:53.560
-UH OH, KINDA SOUNDS SERIOUS.

07:53.690 --> 07:55.562
-TOO BAD IT'S NOT MITCH.

07:56.780 --> 07:57.738
SO WHAT'D YOU SAY?

07:57.868 --> 07:59.217
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

07:59.348 --> 08:00.697
I'M GONNA NEED ALL
THE HELP I CAN GET.

08:01.306 --> 08:03.613
-[TECHNO MUSIC]

08:22.502 --> 08:23.285
-WHAT WAS THAT?

08:23.415 --> 08:24.721
-SOME JERK.

08:25.243 --> 08:26.157
-IS EVERYONE OKAY?

08:26.288 --> 08:27.202
-GIRLS: YEAH.

08:29.117 --> 08:30.510
-HEY!

08:32.033 --> 08:33.774
WHAT'S HE DOING?

08:33.904 --> 08:36.732
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

08:45.133 --> 08:46.656
-LOOK OUT GUYS,
HE'S COMING BACK.

08:48.615 --> 08:49.703
STOP!

09:01.802 --> 09:03.325
-APRIL!

09:07.024 --> 09:09.853
APRIL! STOP!

09:09.984 --> 09:14.249
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

09:50.633 --> 09:52.592
-[COUGHING]

09:56.813 --> 09:58.336
-APRIL, ARE YOU OKAY?

09:59.294 --> 10:01.122
-YEAH, I THINK SO.

10:01.252 --> 10:02.427
JUST GIVE ME A SECOND.

10:02.558 --> 10:03.733
-HELP ME SWIM HER IN.

10:16.441 --> 10:18.139
-WE'VE GOTTA TELL THE
LIFEGUARDS ABOUT THIS.

10:18.269 --> 10:19.967
-NO.

10:20.097 --> 10:21.446
-APRIL, THERE'S A LUNATIC
RUNNING AROUND OUT THERE.

10:21.577 --> 10:23.927
-YOU GUYS, WE DON'T
EVEN KNOW WHO IT WAS.

10:24.536 --> 10:26.103
LOOK, NO ONE WAS HURT OKAY,

10:26.234 --> 10:27.844
SO WE DON'T NEED TO MAKE
A BIG DEAL OUT OF THIS.

10:29.498 --> 10:31.239
GUYS, I DON'T
WANT THEM THINKING

10:31.369 --> 10:33.197
I CAN'T HANDLE
MYSELF IN THE WATER.

10:41.205 --> 10:45.383
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

10:56.612 --> 10:58.222
HI, REMEMBER ME?

10:58.353 --> 10:59.789
APRIL GIMINSKI.

10:59.920 --> 11:00.964
-MITCH: SURE, HOW YOU DOING?

11:01.095 --> 11:02.313
-GREAT, AND YOU?

11:02.444 --> 11:04.576
-GREAT, NEVER
HAD A BETTER DAY.

11:05.403 --> 11:06.883
-I JUST WANTED
TO THANK YOU AGAIN

11:07.014 --> 11:08.363
FOR PICKING ME
FOR ROOKIE SCHOOL.

11:08.493 --> 11:09.364
-COME ON UP.

11:16.240 --> 11:18.068
-I STILL CAN'T
BELIEVE THAT I MADE IT.

11:18.199 --> 11:19.896
I MEAN I WAS SO
DEPRESSED AFTER THE RACE

11:20.027 --> 11:22.464
AND NOW IT'S LIKE I
CAN'T STOP SMILING.

11:23.160 --> 11:24.118
-WELL APRIL, YOU
GOT ALL THE MAKINGS

11:24.248 --> 11:25.249
OF A REALLY GOOD LIFEGUARD.

11:26.033 --> 11:27.034
-REALLY?

11:27.164 --> 11:28.513
-WELL ALMOST ALL THE MAKINGS.

11:28.644 --> 11:29.950
YOU NEED TO WORK ON
YOUR INS AND OUTS.

11:30.515 --> 11:31.952
-OH, YEAH.

11:32.082 --> 11:34.041
YOU MEAN GETTING IN
AND OUT OF THE WATER.

11:34.171 --> 11:36.130
I KNOW, I FELT LIKE
A KLUTZ OUT THERE

11:36.260 --> 11:37.958
TRIPPING OVER MY OWN
FEET, BUT YOU KNOW,

11:38.088 --> 11:40.264
WE DON'T GET SURF LIKE
THAT UP AT LAKE WATANABE.

11:40.395 --> 11:41.918
-YOU'LL GET THE HANG OF IT.

11:42.049 --> 11:44.225
-WELL, I JUST WANTED YOU
TO KNOW HOW GRATEFUL I AM.

11:44.355 --> 11:46.183
AND I'M REALLY LOOKING
FORWARD TO THIS SUMMER.

11:46.314 --> 11:48.359
-YOU SHOULD BE, IT'S
A REAL SPECIAL TIME.

11:48.925 --> 11:50.492
I'LL NEVER FORGET
MY ROOKIE SUMMER.

11:51.493 --> 11:52.842
-WHY? WHAT MADE IT SO SPECIAL?

11:52.973 --> 11:54.539
-BEING ON THE BEACH,

11:55.323 --> 11:56.193
HAVING A JOB,

11:58.674 --> 11:59.719
FALLING IN LOVE.

12:04.375 --> 12:05.768
HER NAME WAS BETSY WEXLER.

12:06.900 --> 12:08.815
I WORKED AT TOWER 33,

12:08.945 --> 12:10.294
THE OLD TOWER ON THE BLUFF.

12:15.909 --> 12:17.954
-MITCH: BETSY USED
TO WALK UP AND SUNBATHE

12:18.085 --> 12:19.739
BY MY TOWER EVERYDAY.

12:20.391 --> 12:22.350
I'D SOMETIMES WATCH
HER THROUGH BINOCULARS.

12:23.090 --> 12:25.396
I'D SEEN A LOT OF GIRLS
PATROLLING THE BEACH,

12:25.527 --> 12:27.398
NONE HELD A CANDLE TO BETSY.

12:43.110 --> 12:48.593
♪ SHE IS MY CALIFORNIA DREAM

12:48.724 --> 12:51.640
♪SHE'S LOVELY LIKE A SUMMER BREEZE,

12:51.771 --> 12:54.948
♪BY THE WARM BLUE SEA ♪

12:56.297 --> 13:01.389
♪ SHE IS BETTER THAN ICE CREAM

13:01.519 --> 13:04.174
♪ TASTY LIKE TANGERINES,

13:04.305 --> 13:08.265
♪YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN ♪

13:09.049 --> 13:12.052
♪ ON THE BEACH, UNDER THE SUN ♪

13:12.182 --> 13:15.142
♪ WITHIN REACH, SO MUCH FUN

13:15.272 --> 13:17.144
♪ THE OCEAN BREEZE IS BLOWING

13:17.274 --> 13:21.278
♪ THROUGH HER HAIR

13:21.409 --> 13:24.542
♪ SMELL THE ROSES ON HER SKIN ♪

13:24.673 --> 13:27.937
♪ SO BEAUTIFUL, WHERE TO BEGIN

13:28.068 --> 13:33.029
♪ I CANNOT HELP MYSELF BUT STARE

13:33.682 --> 13:38.556
♪ SHE IS MY CALIFORNIA DREAM ♪

13:38.687 --> 13:41.646
♪ SHE'S HOTTER THAN THE SUNBEAMS

13:41.777 --> 13:44.954
♪ SHINING DOWN ON ME

13:46.216 --> 13:51.395
♪ SHE IS A PEARL IN A SEA OF GIRLS

13:51.526 --> 13:54.746
♪ WITH A SMILE SHE COULD SAVE MY WORLD

13:54.877 --> 13:59.099
♪ LIVING THE DREAM

13:59.229 --> 14:02.363
♪ ON THE SAND, UNDER THE SUN

14:02.493 --> 14:05.235
♪ GETTIN' TAN, SHE'S THE ONE

14:05.366 --> 14:10.937
♪ THE SUMMER BREEZE IS BLOWING THROUGH HER
HAIR ♪

14:11.676 --> 14:14.679
♪ SMELL THE LOTION ON HER SKIN ♪

14:14.810 --> 14:17.030
♪ SO BEAUTIFUL, WHERE TO BEGIN

14:17.160 --> 14:18.945
-MITCH: BETSY AND I
WOULD MEET AT THE JETTY

14:19.075 --> 14:21.034
AND WATCH THE
SAILBOATS COME IN.

14:21.773 --> 14:23.253
I'D GIVE HER MY ROOKIE JACKET

14:23.384 --> 14:25.473
AND WE'D STAY THERE
UNTIL THE SUN WENT DOWN.

14:26.300 --> 14:29.346
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO MEET THERE
THE NIGHT SHE WAS LEAVING,

14:29.869 --> 14:32.262
BUT SHE NEVER SHOWED UP.

14:32.872 --> 14:36.049
NEVER GOT MY JACKET BACK,
OR HEARD FROM BETSY AGAIN.

14:36.614 --> 14:38.007
-APRIL: THAT'S SO SAD.

14:39.008 --> 14:40.749
-MITCH: I'VE ALWAYS
WONDERED WHAT HAPPENED TO HER.

14:41.793 --> 14:43.012
AND THE JACKET.

14:51.803 --> 14:53.457
-APRIL, WHAT'S WRONG?

14:53.588 --> 14:55.851
-NOTHING'S WRONG, I JUST
HAVE A HEADACHE THAT'S ALL.

14:55.982 --> 14:57.635
-ARE YOU SURE
YOU'RE UP FOR THIS?

14:57.766 --> 14:59.246
-WHY ARE YOU GUYS
SO WORRIED ABOUT ME?

14:59.376 --> 15:00.421
I'M FINE.

15:00.551 --> 15:01.509
-OKAY.

15:01.639 --> 15:06.383
-[ROCK MUSIC]

15:11.736 --> 15:13.608
-NEWMIE: ALRIGHT
MACKENZIE, NICE LEG ACTION.

15:13.738 --> 15:14.914
KEEP YOUR WAY FORWARD.

15:15.044 --> 15:16.654
GOOD! GOOD!

15:20.049 --> 15:22.051
-THERE'S A RIP
FORMING SO BE CAREFUL

15:22.182 --> 15:23.400
WHEN YOU GET CLOSE
TO THE PILINGS.

15:24.053 --> 15:25.402
-HOW CAN YOU TELL?

15:25.533 --> 15:27.883
-DISCOLORED WATER,
IRREGULAR WAVE PATTERN,

15:28.753 --> 15:30.059
SEE HOW MUCH BROWN OUT THERE?

15:31.147 --> 15:31.974
-ROOKIE: NOT REALLY.

15:34.716 --> 15:36.500
-HOBIE: LOOK, SEE WHERE
IT'S FLATTENING OUT?

15:37.284 --> 15:38.328
-ROOKIE: OH WAIT, NOW I DO.

15:39.199 --> 15:40.765
-APRIL, ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

15:40.896 --> 15:42.202
YOU LOOK A LITTLE PALE.

15:42.767 --> 15:45.422
-NO, I'M FINE, I'M JUST
TRYING TO CONCENTRATE.

15:46.119 --> 15:47.947
-ALRIGHT, WHO'S UP NEXT?

15:48.860 --> 15:50.166
-GUESS THAT'S ME.

15:50.297 --> 15:51.863
-NEWMIE: COME ON,
LET'S GO! LETS GO!

15:52.516 --> 15:53.604
COME ON, COME ON!

15:53.735 --> 15:54.518
LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

15:54.649 --> 15:56.346
HUSTLE, COME ON!

15:57.217 --> 15:59.654
ALRIGHT, COME ON I WANNA
SEE YOUR KNEES UP GIMINSKI,

15:59.784 --> 16:01.438
ALL THE WAY TO YOUR CHIN.

16:13.624 --> 16:15.757
NICE FORM, BUT YOU
CAN'T SEE THE VICTIM

16:15.887 --> 16:17.193
WITH YOUR HEAD IN THE WATER.

16:17.324 --> 16:18.890
A LIFEGUARD SWIMS
WITH HER HEAD UP.

16:19.500 --> 16:20.501
HEAD UP!

16:24.548 --> 16:26.028
HEY, BUCHANNON, YOU'RE UP!

16:27.029 --> 16:28.988
COME ON, HUSTLE BUCHANNON!

16:30.206 --> 16:31.686
COME ON, LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

16:31.816 --> 16:32.904
LET'S GO!

16:34.123 --> 16:35.951
WHAT IS THIS, SLOW MOTION?

16:36.082 --> 16:38.606
I WANNA SEE THOSE LEGS
PUMPING BUCHANNON!

16:41.826 --> 16:44.655
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

17:32.181 --> 17:34.096
-HOBIE: APRIL, ARE YOU OKAY?

17:36.316 --> 17:37.186
-JUST, I DON'T KNOW.

17:39.232 --> 17:40.276
YEAH.

17:42.844 --> 17:45.716
-APRIL! APRIL, ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

17:48.502 --> 17:49.459
WHAT'S WRONG?

17:49.590 --> 17:50.895
NEWMIE!

17:53.594 --> 17:55.074
-APRIL: I CAN'T MAKE IT HOBIE.

18:04.996 --> 18:05.997
-APRIL!

18:06.128 --> 18:09.305
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

18:29.891 --> 18:31.458
-NEWMIE: SUPPORT
HER WEIGHT HOBIE,

18:31.588 --> 18:32.241
I'M GONNA TRY AND
GET HER FOOT OUT.

18:35.418 --> 18:36.463
ALRIGHT, EASY DOWN, GOT HER?

18:36.593 --> 18:37.942
-GOT HER.

18:38.073 --> 18:39.509
-THAT'S IT, HOLD HER NECK.

18:39.640 --> 18:41.032
SUPPORT HER NECK.

18:42.860 --> 18:44.123
ALRIGHT, KEEP HER SUPPORTED.

18:45.994 --> 18:48.562
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

18:51.608 --> 18:54.045
-[SIRENS]

18:55.786 --> 18:57.136
KEEP HER HEAD STRAIGHT.

18:58.746 --> 18:59.834
KEEP HER HEAD STRAIGHT.

19:08.059 --> 19:09.670
-OKAY, WE'RE
READY WITH THE BOARD.

19:09.800 --> 19:10.932
-I'VE GOT THE C-COLLAR.

19:21.725 --> 19:23.205
-ALRIGHT, KEEP
TRACTION ON HER HEAD

19:23.336 --> 19:24.685
UNTIL WE GET THAT COLLAR ON.

19:24.815 --> 19:25.860
-HOBIE: I GOT IT.

19:30.125 --> 19:31.170
-THANK YOU HOBIE.

19:32.562 --> 19:33.781
-YOU'RE GONNA BE ALRIGHT.

19:40.091 --> 19:41.267
-ALRIGHT, SHE ALL SECURE?

19:41.397 --> 19:42.224
-SECURE.

19:42.355 --> 19:43.965
-ONE, TWO, THREE, UP.

19:45.619 --> 19:47.186
ALRIGHT, EASY, EASY NOW.

19:48.970 --> 19:54.018
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

19:55.672 --> 20:00.155
-[SIRENS]

20:02.375 --> 20:04.159
-SO APRIL SUFFERED A SLIGHT
CONCUSSION, THAT'S IT HUH?

20:04.290 --> 20:05.900
-YEAH, SHE'S ONLY GONNA
BE OUT FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS

20:06.030 --> 20:07.423
THANKS TO HOBIE.

20:07.554 --> 20:08.859
YOU KNOW, YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT HIM.

20:08.990 --> 20:09.817
HE'S GOT LIFEGUARDING
IN HIS BLOOD.

20:10.383 --> 20:11.558
WHAT'S UP WITH MANNY?

20:11.688 --> 20:13.212
-WELL I WENT AND
SAW HIS MOTHER,

20:13.342 --> 20:15.605
SHE WASN'T SURPRISED THAT
HE FLEW OFF THE HANDLE.

20:16.258 --> 20:17.390
SHE SAID BECOMING A LIFEGUARD

20:17.520 --> 20:19.305
WAS ALL HE SEEMED
TO CARE ABOUT.

20:19.435 --> 20:21.263
-YOU KNOW I HATE TO LOSE A KID
LIKE THAT ON A TECHNICALITY.

20:21.394 --> 20:22.960
WITH THESE NEW CONTACT LENSES

20:23.091 --> 20:25.224
A PERSON'S UNCORRECTED
VISION REALLY DOESN'T MATTER.

20:35.843 --> 20:36.757
-HEY.

20:45.505 --> 20:46.897
-MITCH, I WANNA APOLOGIZE

20:48.116 --> 20:49.248
FOR THE THINGS THAT I SAID,

20:50.597 --> 20:52.076
AND THE WAY THAT I BEHAVED.

20:54.209 --> 20:56.037
I AM ASHAMED OF MYSELF,

20:57.517 --> 20:59.170
AND I WANT TO HELP PAY
FOR ALL OF THE DAMAGES

20:59.301 --> 21:00.302
THAT I DID TO YOUR OFFICE.

21:00.433 --> 21:01.608
-FORGET ABOUT IT.

21:01.738 --> 21:03.218
-NO, REALLY.

21:03.349 --> 21:04.480
-DON'T WORRY,
IT'S IN THE BUDGET.

21:04.611 --> 21:05.742
FORGET ABOUT IT.

21:09.964 --> 21:11.313
-MITCH, I DIDN'T COME
HERE JUST FOR THAT.

21:13.446 --> 21:14.534
I WAS HOPING THAT...

21:17.101 --> 21:19.669
THAT YOU'LL STILL RECOMMEND
ME TO THE SAND AND SEA CLUB.

21:22.716 --> 21:24.065
-YOU SURE YOU WANT THAT?

21:24.718 --> 21:25.980
-IT'LL ONLY BE FOR A YEAR.

21:27.111 --> 21:29.288
I'VE DECIDED TO PUT
COLLEGE OFF FOR A WHILE,

21:29.897 --> 21:32.639
AND WORK FULL TIME SO THAT I
CAN PAY FOR THAT LASER SURGERY

21:32.769 --> 21:34.075
HOBIE WAS TALKING TO ME ABOUT.

21:34.205 --> 21:35.946
-MANNY, HOLD ON A MINUTE, LOOK.

21:36.077 --> 21:40.299
-MITCH, ALL MY LIFE, I NEVER
FELT LIKE I BELONGED ANYWHERE.

21:41.996 --> 21:43.693
UNTIL I CAME TO BAYWATCH.

21:44.781 --> 21:47.436
I SAID TO MYSELF FROM
DAY ONE, THAT I WOULD DO

21:47.567 --> 21:50.091
WHATEVER IT TAKES TO
BECOME A COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

21:52.354 --> 21:54.313
AND DESPITE EVERYTHING
THAT'S GONE DOWN,

21:56.358 --> 21:57.794
I STILL FEEL THAT WAY.

21:59.709 --> 22:00.971
I STILL WANT IT.

22:02.451 --> 22:04.323
MITCH, NOW I WANT
IT MORE THAN EVER.

22:08.892 --> 22:12.461
-[ROCK MUSIC]

22:12.592 --> 22:14.158
-♪ I GOTTA KEEP IT REAL

22:14.289 --> 22:15.246
♪ I GOTTA FEEL

22:15.377 --> 22:17.727
♪ I WANT TO BE EVERYTHING YOU FEAR

22:17.858 --> 22:19.294
♪ I WANNA SHAKE IT

22:19.425 --> 22:22.906
♪ WANNA BREAK IT
GOTTA MOVE IT TILL I MAKE IT ♪

22:23.037 --> 22:25.431
♪ I'M RIDING HIGH ON THE SKY

22:25.561 --> 22:28.259
♪ AND I'M CRUISING OUT OF SIGHT

22:28.390 --> 22:32.525
♪ SO TELL ME IF YOU'RE WITH ME COZ WE'RE
RUNNING OUT OF TIME ♪

22:33.177 --> 22:37.486
♪ YOU MOVE SO FAST WANNA CATCH YOUR WAVE ♪

22:38.226 --> 22:43.187
♪ YOU LIGHT ME UP AND I WANT YOU NEXT TO
ME ♪

22:43.318 --> 22:47.801
♪ I DON'T CARE IF YOU MISBEHAVE

22:47.931 --> 22:52.371
♪ WON'T YOU GIVE IT TO ME WONT YOU RESCUE
ME ♪

22:52.501 --> 22:54.416
♪ COS I'M ON FIRE

22:57.071 --> 22:59.116
♪ I'M RIDING HIGHER

23:01.945 --> 23:04.295
♪ COS I'M ON FIRE

23:06.820 --> 23:08.996
♪ I'M RIDING HIGHER

23:10.258 --> 23:11.477
♪ HIGHER

23:41.985 --> 23:43.552
-LANI: APRIL, DOESN'T
THAT LOOK LIKE THE GUY

23:43.683 --> 23:44.814
THAT TRIED TO RUN US DOWN?

23:46.468 --> 23:47.687
-I CAN'T TELL FROM HERE.

23:49.166 --> 23:51.734
-I THINK IT IS, I
THINK THAT'S HIM!

23:52.518 --> 23:53.519
COME ON!

23:56.304 --> 23:59.220
-GOTTA USE THE TRIM
IN CHOPPY WATER.

23:59.350 --> 24:00.308
GOTTA KEEP THE NOSE UP.

24:00.439 --> 24:01.396
-WHAT'S UP LADIES?

24:01.527 --> 24:03.224
-I'VE GOT A QUESTION FOR YOU.

24:03.354 --> 24:04.660
CAN A LIFEGUARD MAKE AN ARREST?

24:05.705 --> 24:07.010
-DEPENDS ON THE SITUATION, WHY?

24:09.056 --> 24:10.840
-THE OTHER DAY WHEN
WE WERE OUT ON A SWIM,

24:11.624 --> 24:13.539
A GUY ON A WAVE
RUNNER ATTACKED ME.

24:13.669 --> 24:16.455
-HE DRAGGED APRIL BY THE
TETHER OF HER RESCUE CAN.

24:16.585 --> 24:18.544
I THINK THAT'S HOW SHE
GOT THE CONCUSSION.

24:18.674 --> 24:20.197
-WHY DIDN'T YOU
GUYS REPORT THIS?

24:20.894 --> 24:24.332
-SHE DIDN'T WANT US TO TELL,
SO NO ONE SAID ANYTHING.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.377
-WE THINK THAT'S
HIM OVER THERE.

24:26.508 --> 24:28.162
-ONE RESCUE CRAFT
THIS IS MADISON,

24:28.292 --> 24:29.903
NEWMAN AND I ARE IN PURSUIT

24:30.033 --> 24:32.035
OF A FELONY SUSPECT ON A
WAVE RUNNER AT BREAK WATER.

24:40.783 --> 24:42.132
-NEWMIE: STOP!

24:42.263 --> 24:44.091
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

25:37.144 --> 25:38.058
HEY!

25:42.018 --> 25:42.932
HEY!

25:43.063 --> 25:44.151
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

25:59.427 --> 26:01.516
-CODY: TAKE YOUR
HAND OFF THE GAS!

26:01.647 --> 26:03.083
DROP DOWN!

26:03.213 --> 26:05.694
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

26:21.710 --> 26:27.324
-[SIRENS]

26:41.382 --> 26:42.992
THIS IS YOUR LAST WARNING!

26:43.123 --> 26:44.124
-MAN: GO TO HELL!

26:44.254 --> 26:46.692
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

27:06.842 --> 27:10.063
-[SIRENS]

27:10.193 --> 27:12.979
-[GRUNTING]

27:19.812 --> 27:22.379
-THAT'S RICHIE, THE
GUY THAT MITCH EXPELLED.

27:23.250 --> 27:25.731
I GUESS YOU WON'T BE TRYING OUT
FOR ROOKIE SCHOOL NEXT YEAR.

27:30.039 --> 27:31.998
-CODY: LET'S GO,
GET HIM ON THE SCARAB.

27:48.362 --> 27:49.537
-HOPE YOU'RE READY MANNY,

27:49.668 --> 27:50.799
YOU GOT A LOT OF
CATCHING UP TO DO.

27:50.930 --> 27:52.758
-MITCH, I DON'T
KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

27:52.888 --> 27:55.195
I JUST HOPE THAT SOMEDAY I
CAN PAY YOU BACK FOR THIS.

27:55.325 --> 27:56.109
-JUST GIVE ME 100%.

27:56.239 --> 27:57.588
-OH YOU CAN COUNT ON IT.

27:57.719 --> 27:59.503
AND THANKS FOR BELIEVING IN ME.

28:01.723 --> 28:02.681
-HOBIE: HI.

28:03.290 --> 28:04.508
WHAT'S UP MAN?

28:07.163 --> 28:08.382
-YOU WANTED TO SEE US?

28:09.470 --> 28:10.689
-YEAH I DID.

28:12.081 --> 28:13.082
HAVE A SEAT.

28:22.004 --> 28:24.441
YOU REALIZE I'VE GOT GROUNDS
FOR YOUR IMMEDIATE DISMISSAL

28:24.572 --> 28:25.921
FROM ROOKIE SCHOOL DON'T YOU?

28:26.835 --> 28:29.011
-PLEASE DON'T BLAME
THEM, IT WAS MY FAULT.

28:29.142 --> 28:31.448
I MADE THEM PROMISE
NOT TO SAY ANYTHING.

28:34.451 --> 28:39.848
-LADIES, YOU NOT ONLY
JEOPARDIZED BECOMING LIFEGUARDS,

28:41.110 --> 28:42.503
YOU JEOPARDIZED A LIFE.

28:43.809 --> 28:46.202
BEING A LIFEGUARD'S
A 24 HOUR A DAY JOB.

28:47.595 --> 28:48.727
WE HAVE A SAYING AROUND HERE.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.426
ONCE A LIFEGUARD
ALWAYS A LIFEGUARD.

28:52.948 --> 28:54.167
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

28:54.950 --> 28:57.692
IT MEANS BEING PREPARED
FOR ANY EMERGENCY, ANYTIME,

28:57.823 --> 29:00.347
WHENEVER AND
WHEREVER IT HAPPENS.

29:01.087 --> 29:03.785
WHENEVER YOU WITNESS AN
INCIDENT, WHETHER YOU'RE ON DUTY

29:03.916 --> 29:06.788
OR NOT, YOU REPORT
IT IMMEDIATELY.

29:06.919 --> 29:08.877
YOU DO NOT KEEP IT A SECRET.

29:13.795 --> 29:15.101
NOW DO YOU THINK
YOU ALL CAN HANDLE

29:15.231 --> 29:16.885
THAT KIND OF RESPONSIBILITY?

29:17.016 --> 29:18.321
-ALL: YES, SIR.

29:21.194 --> 29:22.499
-I HAD A FEELING
YOU'D SAY THAT.

29:24.458 --> 29:25.633
I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.

29:27.504 --> 29:28.679
SEE YOU IN THE WATER.

29:31.160 --> 29:35.208
-[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

29:38.515 --> 29:39.865
-CONGRATULATIONS.

29:40.735 --> 29:42.258
YOU SHOULD ALL BE VERY
PROUD OF YOURSELVES

29:42.389 --> 29:43.782
FOR MAKING IT THIS FAR.

29:46.088 --> 29:49.396
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I'M VERY SURPRISED

29:49.526 --> 29:51.050
TO SEE MANY OF YOU STILL HERE.

29:54.662 --> 29:56.969
THIS IS ABOUT THE FINEST GROUP
OF ROOKIES I'VE EVER SEEN.

29:58.100 --> 29:59.275
THAT'S THE GOOD NEWS.

30:00.059 --> 30:04.150
THE BAD NEWS, THERE ARE ONLY
10 OPENINGS THIS SEASON.

30:05.716 --> 30:10.373
BASED ON OUR EVALUATIONS,
AND YOUR TEST SCORES,

30:11.026 --> 30:13.942
PRETTY MUCH PUTS EVERYBODY
IN THE SAME BOAT.

30:14.682 --> 30:19.426
SO, IT COMES DOWN TO THE
FINAL RUNNING OF THE GAUNTLET.

30:22.342 --> 30:23.299
ON YOUR MARK!

30:24.735 --> 30:27.695
REMEMBER EVERYTHING YOU
LEARNED, STAY FOCUSED.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.002
ALRIGHT, GET SET!

30:33.353 --> 30:34.180
-[GUNSHOT]

30:34.310 --> 30:37.313
-[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

30:55.418 --> 31:00.336
-[ROCK MUSIC]

33:04.765 --> 33:06.071
-SHE'S GONNA MAKE IT.

33:08.464 --> 33:09.465
-WAY TO GO.

33:11.467 --> 33:13.469
YOU GOT IT, YOU GOT IT.

33:14.514 --> 33:19.519
-[ROCK MUSIC]

34:53.960 --> 34:56.442
-[CHEERING]

35:01.490 --> 35:02.752
-COME ON HOBSTER!

35:05.712 --> 35:07.192
YEAH!

35:08.454 --> 35:09.455
-[CHEERING]

35:09.585 --> 35:11.674
THAT'S MY BOY!
GOOD JOB MANNY.

35:11.805 --> 35:12.893
GOOD JOB.

35:13.459 --> 35:14.895
-LIFEGUARD: ARIGHT CHERYL!

35:16.984 --> 35:18.028
-ALRIGHT.

35:18.899 --> 35:23.599
-[CHEERING]

35:36.612 --> 35:37.483
-I'M ALL OUT.

35:37.613 --> 35:38.745
-I'VE GOT ONE LEFT!

35:39.354 --> 35:40.529
-ROOKIES: APRIL!

35:40.660 --> 35:46.013
-[CHEERING]

36:12.866 --> 36:17.697
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

36:42.504 --> 36:44.419
-YEAH, IT'S BUCHANNON,
GET ME GIMINSKI.

36:44.550 --> 36:45.812
I'VE GOT A
FEELING SHE'S PLAYING

36:45.942 --> 36:47.770
A LITTLE PRACTICAL
JOKE ON ME HERE.

36:48.597 --> 36:49.555
-MITCH.

36:54.212 --> 36:55.561
-NEVER MIND.

36:57.998 --> 36:58.912
BETSY?

36:59.695 --> 37:01.610
-HAD A FEELING YOU'D
STILL BE AT THE BEACH.

37:01.741 --> 37:02.655
HOW ARE YOU?

37:06.441 --> 37:07.442
-I'M FINE, I...

37:08.835 --> 37:10.402
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

37:10.532 --> 37:12.230
-I'M IN TOWN FOR A CONVENTION.

37:14.144 --> 37:15.102
-WOW, THAT'S AMAZING.

37:15.233 --> 37:17.713
I WAS JUST THINKING ABOUT YOU.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.327
YOU LOOK GREAT.

37:23.632 --> 37:25.155
-YOU HAVEN'T CHANGED A BIT.

37:26.244 --> 37:28.158
I BET THE JACKET STILL FITS.

37:30.770 --> 37:31.945
GUESS YOU'RE WONDERING WHY

37:32.075 --> 37:33.512
IT'S TAKEN ME SO
LONG TO RETURN IT.

37:39.779 --> 37:41.259
I WAS ON MY WAY TO
MEET YOU AND THERE WAS

37:41.389 --> 37:43.957
A BIG ACCIDENT ON
THE COAST HIGHWAY.

37:44.087 --> 37:46.220
THE TRAFFIC WAS
BACKED UP FOR MILES.

37:46.742 --> 37:49.832
I HELPED TREAT THE VICTIMS
UNTIL THE PARAMEDICS GOT THERE.

37:49.963 --> 37:52.313
BY THE TIME IT ALL CLEARED
UP IT WAS TOO LATE,

37:52.444 --> 37:54.097
I WOULD'VE MISSED MY FLIGHT.

37:55.490 --> 37:56.926
-WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL?

37:57.840 --> 37:59.320
-I WAS GOING TO.

37:59.451 --> 38:03.672
THEN, WHEN I GOT TO SCHOOL
EVERYTHING CHANGED SUDDENLY.

38:04.412 --> 38:06.675
I MET THIS UPPER
CLASSMAN, AND WELL...

38:08.198 --> 38:10.244
GUESS I COULDN'T FIND
THE RIGHT WORDS, OR,

38:11.201 --> 38:12.377
MAYBE I CHICKENED OUT.

38:14.379 --> 38:15.945
I'M SORRY IF I HURT YOU.

38:17.817 --> 38:19.514
HOPE IT'S NOT TOO
LATE TO MAKE AMENDS.

38:24.171 --> 38:25.390
-LOOK, I UH...

38:27.435 --> 38:29.002
I CAN'T TALK ABOUT THIS NOW.

38:30.917 --> 38:32.484
I'LL BE OFF DUTY
IN A COUPLE HOURS.

38:32.614 --> 38:34.529
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT,
I'LL MEET YOU AT THE...

38:39.055 --> 38:40.318
YOU KNOW WHERE TO MEET.

38:41.449 --> 38:43.321
DON'T STAND ME UP THIS TIME.

38:46.585 --> 38:50.328
-[GENTLE MUSIC]

39:16.005 --> 39:17.006
-I CAN'T.

39:19.444 --> 39:21.533
WHEN I SAID I WAS
AT A CONVENTION,

39:21.663 --> 39:24.623
I DIDN'T MENTION IT WAS
MY HUSBAND'S CONVENTION.

39:27.452 --> 39:29.279
-NO, YOU DIDN'T.

39:31.151 --> 39:32.674
-I DON'T GO TO CONVENTIONS.

39:33.545 --> 39:35.547
I STAY AT HOME AND
RAISE OUR TWO KIDS.

39:37.331 --> 39:39.202
THEY'RE ALL BACK AT THE
HOTEL WAITING FOR ME.

39:40.682 --> 39:41.814
I JUST...

39:43.642 --> 39:46.427
I JUST NEEDED TO FIND OUT
WHAT I MISSED ALL THESE YEARS.

39:50.866 --> 39:56.045
-WELL, MAYBE SOMEDAY WE'LL
GET OUR TIMING RIGHT, HUH?

40:13.498 --> 40:16.762
-ANYWAY, IT'S
CLASSIC, BUT UM...

40:16.892 --> 40:17.850
-HOB!

40:18.372 --> 40:19.504
-SEE YOU TONIGHT.

40:20.679 --> 40:22.245
-BYE.

40:22.376 --> 40:26.685
-WELL, FOR THE SECOND
TIME IN LIFEGUARD HISTORY,

40:26.815 --> 40:29.296
A BUCHANNON HAS WON
ROOKIE OF THE YEAR HONORS.

40:29.427 --> 40:30.253
-OH YEAH!

40:30.384 --> 40:32.125
DIDN'T THINK I'D
MAKE IT DID YA?

40:32.255 --> 40:33.692
-NAH, I KNEW YOU HAD IT IN YA,

40:33.822 --> 40:35.345
I JUST DIDN'T KNOW IF
IT WAS GONNA COME OUT.

40:35.476 --> 40:37.260
-WHY LET ALL THIS TALENT
GO TO WASTE, RIGHT?

40:37.391 --> 40:38.958
-MY SENTIMENTS EXACTLY.

40:39.088 --> 40:40.263
YOU KNOW AS ROOKIE OF THE YEAR

40:40.394 --> 40:41.090
YOU GET TO CHOOSE
YOUR OWN BEACH.

40:41.221 --> 40:42.831
-YEAH I KNOW.

40:42.962 --> 40:46.792
AND SINCE IT'S MY DECISION,
I WANNA WORK AT ZUMA.

40:47.488 --> 40:49.272
-ZUMA?

40:49.403 --> 40:51.013
-YEAH, I FIGURE WITH ALL THE
TIME ME AND YOU SPEND TOGETHER

40:51.144 --> 40:53.494
AROUND THE HOUSE, IT'D BE
BETTER FOR THE BOTH OF US

40:53.625 --> 40:55.453
WITH YOU AT BAYWATCH
AND ME AT ZUMA.

40:55.583 --> 40:58.238
-WELL I GUESS I UNDERSTAND,
I JUST WISH YOU'D TOLD ME,

40:58.368 --> 41:00.153
YOU KNOW, BEFORE
I BECAME CAPTAIN.

41:01.284 --> 41:02.634
-CAPTAIN? BUT I THOUGHT...

41:02.764 --> 41:04.287
-I CHANGED MY MIND.

41:04.418 --> 41:06.812
AS OF MONDAY MORNING I'M
GONNA BE CONTROLLING EVERY

41:06.942 --> 41:10.076
GRAIN OF SAND FROM HERMOSA
BEACH TO VENTURA COUNTY LINE.

41:10.206 --> 41:11.860
-GREAT. THAT'S JUST GREAT.

41:11.991 --> 41:13.949
YOU'RE GONNA BE LOOKING OVER
MY SHOULDER EVERY DAY NOW.

41:14.080 --> 41:15.124
-EVERY DAY.

41:17.126 --> 41:20.521
-THANKS A LOT, YOU KNOW YOU
JUST RUINED MY WHOLE SUMMER.

41:20.652 --> 41:23.263
-I'LL BE THERE, LOOKING
OVER YOUR SHOULDER EVERY DAY.

41:23.393 --> 41:26.266
BOSSING YOU AROUND,
TELLING YOU WHAT TO DO.

41:26.396 --> 41:28.137
-HOBIE: COMPLETELY RUINED!

41:28.268 --> 41:30.009
-MITCH: I'LL BE THE FIRST
PERSON YOU SEE IN THE MORNING,

41:30.139 --> 41:31.706
I'LL BE THE LAST PERSON
YOU SEE AT NIGHT.

41:31.837 --> 41:34.317
I'M GOING TO RUIN
YOUR LIFE FOREVER!

41:34.448 --> 41:35.623
-HOBIE: I WON'T
EVEN BE ABLE TO FLIRT

41:35.754 --> 41:37.146
WITH ANY GIRLS ON THE BEACH.

41:37.277 --> 41:38.626
-YOU CAN FLIRT WITH
GIRLS ON THE BEACH.

41:38.757 --> 41:39.714
-HOBIE: OH, THANKS.

41:39.845 --> 41:40.715
-MITCH: BUT NOT ON MY BEACH.

41:40.846 --> 41:42.195
-HOBIE: AH!

41:42.325 --> 41:43.544
-MITCH: NO, ON THAT
BEACH UP THERE...

41:44.545 --> 41:46.852
-[END THEME MUSIC]
